HEADWORD: Denitrification
<hw>De*ni`tri*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act
or process of freeing from nitrogen; also, the condition resulting from
the removal of nitrogen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

